702303f-a.title: Brooklyn: 3rd Avenue - 65th Street
702303f-a.text:
Third Ave., at the N.E. corner of 65th Street, showing the old Station
on the New York and Hempstead branch of the Long 1sland R.R.  In 1890 it
was known as John Warth's Hotel.  In 1929 a 1-story frame building occupied
by the Bayview Laundry is on the site.  )In 1922 the Third Ave. Elevated
line had not been extended to this point).
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Ccllection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
